2284/// When a match is complete, this method updates uses of interior chain results
2285/// to use the new results.
2286void SelectionDAGISel::UpdateChains(
2287 SDNode *NodeToMatch, SDValue InputChain,
2288 SmallVectorImpl<SDNode *> &ChainNodesMatched, bool isMorphNodeTo) {
2289 SmallVector<SDNode*, 4> NowDeadNodes;
2290
2291 // Now that all the normal results are replaced, we replace the chain and
2292 // glue results if present.
2293 if (!ChainNodesMatched.empty()) {
2294 assert(InputChain.getNode() &&
2295 "Matched input chains but didn't produce a chain");
2296 // Loop over all of the nodes we matched that produced a chain result.
2297 // Replace all the chain results with the final chain we ended up with.
2298 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ChainNodesMatched.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2299 SDNode *ChainNode = ChainNodesMatched[i];
2300 // If ChainNode is null, it's because we replaced it on a previous
2301 // iteration and we cleared it out of the map. Just skip it.
2302 if (!ChainNode)
2303 continue;
2304
2305 assert(ChainNode->getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE &&
2306 "Deleted node left in chain");
2307
2308 // Don't replace the results of the root node if we're doing a
2309 // MorphNodeTo.
2310 if (ChainNode == NodeToMatch && isMorphNodeTo)
2311 continue;
2312
2313 SDValue ChainVal = SDValue(ChainNode, ChainNode->getNumValues()-1);
2314 if (ChainVal.getValueType() == MVT::Glue)
2315 ChainVal = ChainVal.getValue(ChainVal->getNumValues()-2);
2316 assert(ChainVal.getValueType() == MVT::Other && "Not a chain?");
2317 SelectionDAG::DAGNodeDeletedListener NDL(
2318 *CurDAG, [&](SDNode *N, SDNode *E) {
2319 std::replace(ChainNodesMatched.begin(), ChainNodesMatched.end(), N,
2320 static_cast<SDNode *>(nullptr));
2321 });
2322 if (ChainNode->getOpcode() != ISD::TokenFactor)
2323 ReplaceUses(ChainVal, InputChain);
2324
2325 // If the node became dead and we haven't already seen it, delete it.
2326 if (ChainNode != NodeToMatch && ChainNode->use_empty() &&
2327 !std::count(NowDeadNodes.begin(), NowDeadNodes.end(), ChainNode))
2328 NowDeadNodes.push_back(ChainNode);
2329 }
2330 }
2331
2332 if (!NowDeadNodes.empty())
2333 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNodes(NowDeadNodes);
2334
2335 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ISEL: Match complete!\n");
2336}
2337
2338/// HandleMergeInputChains - This implements the OPC_EmitMergeInputChains
2339/// operation for when the pattern matched at least one node with a chains. The
2340/// input vector contains a list of all of the chained nodes that we match. We
2341/// must determine if this is a valid thing to cover (i.e. matching it won't
2342/// induce cycles in the DAG) and if so, creating a TokenFactor node. that will
2343/// be used as the input node chain for the generated nodes.
2344static SDValue
2345HandleMergeInputChains(SmallVectorImpl<SDNode*> &ChainNodesMatched,
2346 SelectionDAG *CurDAG) {
2347
2348 SmallPtrSet<const SDNode *, 16> Visited;
2349 SmallVector<const SDNode *, 8> Worklist;
2350 SmallVector<SDValue, 3> InputChains;
2351 unsigned int Max = 8192;
2352
2353 // Quick exit on trivial merge.
2354 if (ChainNodesMatched.size() == 1)
2355 return ChainNodesMatched[0]->getOperand(0);
2356
2357 // Add chains that aren't already added (internal). Peek through
2358 // token factors.
2359 std::function<void(const SDValue)> AddChains = [&](const SDValue V) {
2360 if (V.getValueType() != MVT::Other)
2361 return;
2362 if (V->getOpcode() == ISD::EntryToken)
2363 return;
2364 if (!Visited.insert(V.getNode()).second)
2365 return;
2366 if (V->getOpcode() == ISD::TokenFactor) {
2367 for (const SDValue &Op : V->op_values())
2368 AddChains(Op);
2369 } else
2370 InputChains.push_back(V);
2371 };
2372
2373 for (auto *N : ChainNodesMatched) {
2374 Worklist.push_back(N);
2375 Visited.insert(N);
2376 }
2377
2378 while (!Worklist.empty())
2379 AddChains(Worklist.pop_back_val()->getOperand(0));
2380
2381 // Skip the search if there are no chain dependencies.
2382 if (InputChains.size() == 0)
2383 return CurDAG->getEntryNode();
2384
2385 // If one of these chains is a successor of input, we must have a
2386 // node that is both the predecessor and successor of the
2387 // to-be-merged nodes. Fail.
2388 Visited.clear();
2389 for (SDValue V : InputChains)
2390 Worklist.push_back(V.getNode());
2391
2392 for (auto *N : ChainNodesMatched)
2393 if (SDNode::hasPredecessorHelper(N, Visited, Worklist, Max, true))
2394 return SDValue();
2395
2396 // Return merged chain.
2397 if (InputChains.size() == 1)
2398 return InputChains[0];
2399 return CurDAG->getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SDLoc(ChainNodesMatched[0]),
2400 MVT::Other, InputChains);
2401}
2402
2403/// MorphNode - Handle morphing a node in place for the selector.
2404SDNode *SelectionDAGISel::
2405MorphNode(SDNode *Node, unsigned TargetOpc, SDVTList VTList,
2406 ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, unsigned EmitNodeInfo) {
2407 // It is possible we're using MorphNodeTo to replace a node with no
2408 // normal results with one that has a normal result (or we could be
2409 // adding a chain) and the input could have glue and chains as well.
2410 // In this case we need to shift the operands down.
2411 // FIXME: This is a horrible hack and broken in obscure cases, no worse
2412 // than the old isel though.
2413 int OldGlueResultNo = -1, OldChainResultNo = -1;
2414
2415 unsigned NTMNumResults = Node->getNumValues();
2416 if (Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-1) == MVT::Glue) {
2417 OldGlueResultNo = NTMNumResults-1;
2418 if (NTMNumResults != 1 &&
2419 Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-2) == MVT::Other)
2420 OldChainResultNo = NTMNumResults-2;
2421 } else if (Node->getValueType(NTMNumResults-1) == MVT::Other)
2422 OldChainResultNo = NTMNumResults-1;
2423
2424 // Call the underlying SelectionDAG routine to do the transmogrification. Note
2425 // that this deletes operands of the old node that become dead.
2426 SDNode *Res = CurDAG->MorphNodeTo(Node, ~TargetOpc, VTList, Ops);
2427
2428 // MorphNodeTo can operate in two ways: if an existing node with the
2429 // specified operands exists, it can just return it. Otherwise, it
2430 // updates the node in place to have the requested operands.
2431 if (Res == Node) {
2432 // If we updated the node in place, reset the node ID. To the isel,
2433 // this should be just like a newly allocated machine node.
2434 Res->setNodeId(-1);
2435 }
2436
2437 unsigned ResNumResults = Res->getNumValues();
2438 // Move the glue if needed.
2439 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_GlueOutput) && OldGlueResultNo != -1 &&
2440 (unsigned)OldGlueResultNo != ResNumResults-1)
2441 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, OldGlueResultNo),
2442 SDValue(Res, ResNumResults - 1));
2443
2444 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_GlueOutput) != 0)
2445 --ResNumResults;
2446
2447 // Move the chain reference if needed.
2448 if ((EmitNodeInfo & OPFL_Chain) && OldChainResultNo != -1 &&
2449 (unsigned)OldChainResultNo != ResNumResults-1)
2450 ReplaceUses(SDValue(Node, OldChainResultNo),
2451 SDValue(Res, ResNumResults - 1));
2452
2453 // Otherwise, no replacement happened because the node already exists. Replace
2454 // Uses of the old node with the new one.
2455 if (Res != Node) {
2456 ReplaceNode(Node, Res);
2457 } else {
2458 EnforceNodeIdInvariant(Res);
2459 }
2460
2461 return Res;
2462}

2464/// CheckSame - Implements OP_CheckSame.
2465LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static inline bool
2466CheckSame(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2467 SDValue N,
2468 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode*>> &RecordedNodes) {
2469 // Accept if it is exactly the same as a previously recorded node.
2470 unsigned RecNo = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2471 assert(RecNo < RecordedNodes.size() && "Invalid CheckSame");
2472 return N == RecordedNodes[RecNo].first;
2473}

2475/// CheckChildSame - Implements OP_CheckChildXSame.
2476LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static inline bool
2477CheckChildSame(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2478 SDValue N,
2479 const SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode*>> &RecordedNodes,
2480 unsigned ChildNo) {
2481 if (ChildNo >= N.getNumOperands())
2482 return false; // Match fails if out of range child #.
2483 return ::CheckSame(MatcherTable, MatcherIndex, N.getOperand(ChildNo),
2484 RecordedNodes);
2485}

2503 SDNode *N) {
2504 uint16_t Opc = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2505 Opc |= (unsigned short)MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++] << 8;
2506 return N->getOpcode() == Opc;

2509LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static inline bool
2510CheckType(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex, SDValue N,
2511 const TargetLowering *TLI, const DataLayout &DL) {

2513 if (N.getValueType() == VT) return true;
2514
2515 // Handle the case when VT is iPTR.
2516 return VT == MVT::iPTR && N.getValueType() == TLI->getPointerTy(DL, 0);
2517}

2544LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static inline bool

2548 if (cast<VTSDNode>(N)->getVT() == VT)
2549 return true;

2556LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static inline bool
2557CheckInteger(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2558 SDValue N) {
2559 int64_t Val = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2560 if (Val & 128)
2561 Val = GetVBR(Val, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2562
2563 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N);
2564 return C && C->getSExtValue() == Val;
2565}

2575LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static inline bool
2576CheckAndImm(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2577 SDValue N, const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel) {
2578 int64_t Val = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2579 if (Val & 128)
2580 Val = GetVBR(Val, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2581
2582 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::AND) return false;
2583
2584 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
2585 return C && SDISel.CheckAndMask(N.getOperand(0), C, Val);
2586}
2587
2588LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_ALWAYS_INLINE static inline bool
2589CheckOrImm(const unsigned char *MatcherTable, unsigned &MatcherIndex,
2590 SDValue N, const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel) {
2591 int64_t Val = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2592 if (Val & 128)
2593 Val = GetVBR(Val, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2594
2595 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::OR) return false;
2596
2597 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
2598 return C && SDISel.CheckOrMask(N.getOperand(0), C, Val);
2599}

2601/// IsPredicateKnownToFail - If we know how and can do so without pushing a
2602/// scope, evaluate the current node. If the current predicate is known to
2603/// fail, set Result=true and return anything. If the current predicate is
2604/// known to pass, set Result=false and return the MatcherIndex to continue
2605/// with. If the current predicate is unknown, set Result=false and return the
2606/// MatcherIndex to continue with.
2607static unsigned IsPredicateKnownToFail(const unsigned char *Table,
2608 unsigned Index, SDValue N,
2609 bool &Result,
2610 const SelectionDAGISel &SDISel,
2611 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode*>> &RecordedNodes) {
2612 switch (Table[Index++]) {
2613 default:
2614 Result = false;
2615 return Index-1; // Could not evaluate this predicate.
2616 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckSame:
2617 Result = !::CheckSame(Table, Index, N, RecordedNodes);
2618 return Index;
2619 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Same:
2620 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild1Same:
2621 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2Same:
2622 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild3Same:
2623 Result = !::CheckChildSame(Table, Index, N, RecordedNodes,
2624 Table[Index-1] - SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Same);
2625 return Index;
2626 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckPatternPredicate:
2627 Result = !::CheckPatternPredicate(Table, Index, SDISel);
2628 return Index;
2629 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckPredicate:
2630 Result = !::CheckNodePredicate(Table, Index, SDISel, N.getNode());
2631 return Index;
2632 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckOpcode:
2633 Result = !::CheckOpcode(Table, Index, N.getNode());
2634 return Index;
2635 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckType:
2636 Result = !::CheckType(Table, Index, N, SDISel.TLI,
2637 SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout());
2638 return Index;
2639 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckTypeRes: {
2640 unsigned Res = Table[Index++];
2641 Result = !::CheckType(Table, Index, N.getValue(Res), SDISel.TLI,
2642 SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout());
2643 return Index;
2644 }
2645 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Type:
2646 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild1Type:
2647 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2Type:
2648 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild3Type:
2649 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild4Type:
2650 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild5Type:
2651 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild6Type:
2652 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild7Type:
2653 Result = !::CheckChildType(
2654 Table, Index, N, SDISel.TLI, SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout(),
2655 Table[Index - 1] - SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Type);
2656 return Index;
2657 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckCondCode:
2658 Result = !::CheckCondCode(Table, Index, N);
2659 return Index;
2660 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2CondCode:
2661 Result = !::CheckChild2CondCode(Table, Index, N);
2662 return Index;
2663 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckValueType:
2664 Result = !::CheckValueType(Table, Index, N, SDISel.TLI,
2665 SDISel.CurDAG->getDataLayout());
2666 return Index;
2667 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckInteger:
2668 Result = !::CheckInteger(Table, Index, N);
2669 return Index;
2670 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Integer:
2671 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild1Integer:
2672 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild2Integer:
2673 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild3Integer:
2674 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild4Integer:
2675 Result = !::CheckChildInteger(Table, Index, N,
2676 Table[Index-1] - SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckChild0Integer);
2677 return Index;
2678 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckAndImm:
2679 Result = !::CheckAndImm(Table, Index, N, SDISel);
2680 return Index;
2681 case SelectionDAGISel::OPC_CheckOrImm:
2682 Result = !::CheckOrImm(Table, Index, N, SDISel);
2683 return Index;
2684 }
2685}

2688
2689struct MatchScope {
2690 /// FailIndex - If this match fails, this is the index to continue with.
2691 unsigned FailIndex;
2692
2693 /// NodeStack - The node stack when the scope was formed.
2694 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> NodeStack;
2695
2696 /// NumRecordedNodes - The number of recorded nodes when the scope was formed.
2697 unsigned NumRecordedNodes;
2698
2699 /// NumMatchedMemRefs - The number of matched memref entries.
2700 unsigned NumMatchedMemRefs;
2701
2702 /// InputChain/InputGlue - The current chain/glue
2703 SDValue InputChain, InputGlue;
2704
2705 /// HasChainNodesMatched - True if the ChainNodesMatched list is non-empty.
2706 bool HasChainNodesMatched;
2707};
2708
2709/// \A DAG update listener to keep the matching state
2710/// (i.e. RecordedNodes and MatchScope) uptodate if the target is allowed to
2711/// change the DAG while matching. X86 addressing mode matcher is an example
2712/// for this.
2713class MatchStateUpdater : public SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener
2714{
2715 SDNode **NodeToMatch;
2716 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode *>> &RecordedNodes;
2717 SmallVectorImpl<MatchScope> &MatchScopes;
2718
2719public:
2720 MatchStateUpdater(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDNode **NodeToMatch,
2721 SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode *>> &RN,
2722 SmallVectorImpl<MatchScope> &MS)
2723 : SelectionDAG::DAGUpdateListener(DAG), NodeToMatch(NodeToMatch),
2724 RecordedNodes(RN), MatchScopes(MS) {}
2725
2726 void NodeDeleted(SDNode *N, SDNode *E) override {
2727 // Some early-returns here to avoid the search if we deleted the node or
2728 // if the update comes from MorphNodeTo (MorphNodeTo is the last thing we
2729 // do, so it's unnecessary to update matching state at that point).
2730 // Neither of these can occur currently because we only install this
2731 // update listener during matching a complex patterns.
2732 if (!E || E->isMachineOpcode())
2733 return;
2734 // Check if NodeToMatch was updated.
2735 if (N == *NodeToMatch)
2736 *NodeToMatch = E;
2737 // Performing linear search here does not matter because we almost never
2738 // run this code. You'd have to have a CSE during complex pattern
2739 // matching.
2740 for (auto &I : RecordedNodes)
2741 if (I.first.getNode() == N)
2742 I.first.setNode(E);
2743
2744 for (auto &I : MatchScopes)
2745 for (auto &J : I.NodeStack)
2746 if (J.getNode() == N)
2747 J.setNode(E);
2748 }
2749};
2750
2751} // end anonymous namespace
2752
2753void SelectionDAGISel::SelectCodeCommon(SDNode *NodeToMatch,
2754 const unsigned char *MatcherTable,
2755 unsigned TableSize) {
2756 // FIXME: Should these even be selected? Handle these cases in the caller?
2757 switch (NodeToMatch->getOpcode()) {
2758 default:
2759 break;
2760 case ISD::EntryToken: // These nodes remain the same.
2761 case ISD::BasicBlock:
2762 case ISD::Register:
2763 case ISD::RegisterMask:
2764 case ISD::HANDLENODE:
2765 case ISD::MDNODE_SDNODE:
2766 case ISD::TargetConstant:
2767 case ISD::TargetConstantFP:
2768 case ISD::TargetConstantPool:
2769 case ISD::TargetFrameIndex:
2770 case ISD::TargetExternalSymbol:
2771 case ISD::MCSymbol:
2772 case ISD::TargetBlockAddress:
2773 case ISD::TargetJumpTable:
2774 case ISD::TargetGlobalTLSAddress:
2775 case ISD::TargetGlobalAddress:
2776 case ISD::TokenFactor:
2777 case ISD::CopyFromReg:
2778 case ISD::CopyToReg:
2779 case ISD::EH_LABEL:
2780 case ISD::ANNOTATION_LABEL:
2781 case ISD::LIFETIME_START:
2782 case ISD::LIFETIME_END:
2783 NodeToMatch->setNodeId(-1); // Mark selected.
2784 return;
2785 case ISD::AssertSext:
2786 case ISD::AssertZext:
2787 ReplaceUses(SDValue(NodeToMatch, 0), NodeToMatch->getOperand(0));
2788 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(NodeToMatch);
2789 return;
2790 case ISD::INLINEASM:
2791 case ISD::INLINEASM_BR:
2792 Select_INLINEASM(NodeToMatch,
2793 NodeToMatch->getOpcode() == ISD::INLINEASM_BR);
2794 return;
2795 case ISD::READ_REGISTER:
2796 Select_READ_REGISTER(NodeToMatch);
2797 return;
2798 case ISD::WRITE_REGISTER:
2799 Select_WRITE_REGISTER(NodeToMatch);
2800 return;
2801 case ISD::UNDEF:
2802 Select_UNDEF(NodeToMatch);
2803 return;
2804 }
2805
2806 assert(!NodeToMatch->isMachineOpcode() && "Node already selected!");
2807
2808 // Set up the node stack with NodeToMatch as the only node on the stack.
2809 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NodeStack;
2810 SDValue N = SDValue(NodeToMatch, 0);
2811 NodeStack.push_back(N);
2812
2813 // MatchScopes - Scopes used when matching, if a match failure happens, this
2814 // indicates where to continue checking.
2815 SmallVector<MatchScope, 8> MatchScopes;
2816
2817 // RecordedNodes - This is the set of nodes that have been recorded by the
2818 // state machine. The second value is the parent of the node, or null if the
2819 // root is recorded.
2820 SmallVector<std::pair<SDValue, SDNode*>, 8> RecordedNodes;
2821
2822 // MatchedMemRefs - This is the set of MemRef's we've seen in the input
2823 // pattern.
2824 SmallVector<MachineMemOperand*, 2> MatchedMemRefs;
2825
2826 // These are the current input chain and glue for use when generating nodes.
2827 // Various Emit operations change these. For example, emitting a copytoreg
2828 // uses and updates these.
2829 SDValue InputChain, InputGlue;
2830
2831 // ChainNodesMatched - If a pattern matches nodes that have input/output
2832 // chains, the OPC_EmitMergeInputChains operation is emitted which indicates
2833 // which ones they are. The result is captured into this list so that we can
2834 // update the chain results when the pattern is complete.
2835 SmallVector<SDNode*, 3> ChainNodesMatched;
2836
2837 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "ISEL: Starting pattern match\n");
2838
2839 // Determine where to start the interpreter. Normally we start at opcode #0,
2840 // but if the state machine starts with an OPC_SwitchOpcode, then we
2841 // accelerate the first lookup (which is guaranteed to be hot) with the
2842 // OpcodeOffset table.
2843 unsigned MatcherIndex = 0;
2844
2845 if (!OpcodeOffset.empty()) {
2846 // Already computed the OpcodeOffset table, just index into it.
2847 if (N.getOpcode() < OpcodeOffset.size())
2848 MatcherIndex = OpcodeOffset[N.getOpcode()];
2849 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Initial Opcode index to " << MatcherIndex << "\n");
2850
2851 } else if (MatcherTable[0] == OPC_SwitchOpcode) {
2852 // Otherwise, the table isn't computed, but the state machine does start
2853 // with an OPC_SwitchOpcode instruction. Populate the table now, since this
2854 // is the first time we're selecting an instruction.
2855 unsigned Idx = 1;
2856 while (true) {
2857 // Get the size of this case.
2858 unsigned CaseSize = MatcherTable[Idx++];
2859 if (CaseSize & 128)
2860 CaseSize = GetVBR(CaseSize, MatcherTable, Idx);
2861 if (CaseSize == 0) break;
2862
2863 // Get the opcode, add the index to the table.
2864 uint16_t Opc = MatcherTable[Idx++];
2865 Opc |= (unsigned short)MatcherTable[Idx++] << 8;
2866 if (Opc >= OpcodeOffset.size())
2867 OpcodeOffset.resize((Opc+1)*2);
2868 OpcodeOffset[Opc] = Idx;
2869 Idx += CaseSize;
2870 }
2871
2872 // Okay, do the lookup for the first opcode.
2873 if (N.getOpcode() < OpcodeOffset.size())
2874 MatcherIndex = OpcodeOffset[N.getOpcode()];
2875 }
2876
2877 while (true) {
2878 assert(MatcherIndex < TableSize && "Invalid index");
2879#ifndef NDEBUG
2880 unsigned CurrentOpcodeIndex = MatcherIndex;
2881#endif
2882 BuiltinOpcodes Opcode = (BuiltinOpcodes)MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2883 switch (Opcode) {
2884 case OPC_Scope: {
2885 // Okay, the semantics of this operation are that we should push a scope
2886 // then evaluate the first child. However, pushing a scope only to have
2887 // the first check fail (which then pops it) is inefficient. If we can
2888 // determine immediately that the first check (or first several) will
2889 // immediately fail, don't even bother pushing a scope for them.
2890 unsigned FailIndex;
2891
2892 while (true) {
2893 unsigned NumToSkip = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2894 if (NumToSkip & 128)
2895 NumToSkip = GetVBR(NumToSkip, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
2896 // Found the end of the scope with no match.
2897 if (NumToSkip == 0) {
2898 FailIndex = 0;
2899 break;
2900 }
2901
2902 FailIndex = MatcherIndex+NumToSkip;
2903
2904 unsigned MatcherIndexOfPredicate = MatcherIndex;
2905 (void)MatcherIndexOfPredicate; // silence warning.
2906
2907 // If we can't evaluate this predicate without pushing a scope (e.g. if
2908 // it is a 'MoveParent') or if the predicate succeeds on this node, we
2909 // push the scope and evaluate the full predicate chain.
2910 bool Result;
2911 MatcherIndex = IsPredicateKnownToFail(MatcherTable, MatcherIndex, N,
2912 Result, *this, RecordedNodes);
2913 if (!Result)
2914 break;
2915
2916 LLVM_DEBUG(
2917 dbgs() << " Skipped scope entry (due to false predicate) at "
2918 << "index " << MatcherIndexOfPredicate << ", continuing at "
2919 << FailIndex << "\n");
2920 ++NumDAGIselRetries;
2921
2922 // Otherwise, we know that this case of the Scope is guaranteed to fail,
2923 // move to the next case.
2924 MatcherIndex = FailIndex;
2925 }
2926
2927 // If the whole scope failed to match, bail.
2928 if (FailIndex == 0) break;
2929
2930 // Push a MatchScope which indicates where to go if the first child fails
2931 // to match.
2932 MatchScope NewEntry;
2933 NewEntry.FailIndex = FailIndex;
2934 NewEntry.NodeStack.append(NodeStack.begin(), NodeStack.end());
2935 NewEntry.NumRecordedNodes = RecordedNodes.size();
2936 NewEntry.NumMatchedMemRefs = MatchedMemRefs.size();
2937 NewEntry.InputChain = InputChain;
2938 NewEntry.InputGlue = InputGlue;
2939 NewEntry.HasChainNodesMatched = !ChainNodesMatched.empty();
2940 MatchScopes.push_back(NewEntry);
2941 continue;
2942 }
2943 case OPC_RecordNode: {
2944 // Remember this node, it may end up being an operand in the pattern.
2945 SDNode *Parent = nullptr;
2946 if (NodeStack.size() > 1)
2947 Parent = NodeStack[NodeStack.size()-2].getNode();
2948 RecordedNodes.push_back(std::make_pair(N, Parent));
2949 continue;
2950 }
2951
2952 case OPC_RecordChild0: case OPC_RecordChild1:
2953 case OPC_RecordChild2: case OPC_RecordChild3:
2954 case OPC_RecordChild4: case OPC_RecordChild5:
2955 case OPC_RecordChild6: case OPC_RecordChild7: {
2956 unsigned ChildNo = Opcode-OPC_RecordChild0;
2957 if (ChildNo >= N.getNumOperands())
2958 break; // Match fails if out of range child #.
2959
2960 RecordedNodes.push_back(std::make_pair(N->getOperand(ChildNo),
2961 N.getNode()));
2962 continue;
2963 }
2964 case OPC_RecordMemRef:
2965 if (auto *MN = dyn_cast<MemSDNode>(N))
2966 MatchedMemRefs.push_back(MN->getMemOperand());
2967 else {
2968 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Expected MemSDNode "; N->dump(CurDAG);
2969 dbgs() << '\n');
2970 }
2971
2972 continue;
2973
2974 case OPC_CaptureGlueInput:
2975 // If the current node has an input glue, capture it in InputGlue.
2976 if (N->getNumOperands() != 0 &&
2977 N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands()-1).getValueType() == MVT::Glue)
2978 InputGlue = N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands()-1);
2979 continue;
2980
2981 case OPC_MoveChild: {
2982 unsigned ChildNo = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
2983 if (ChildNo >= N.getNumOperands())
2984 break; // Match fails if out of range child #.
2985 N = N.getOperand(ChildNo);
2986 NodeStack.push_back(N);
2987 continue;
2988 }
2989
2990 case OPC_MoveChild0: case OPC_MoveChild1:
2991 case OPC_MoveChild2: case OPC_MoveChild3:
2992 case OPC_MoveChild4: case OPC_MoveChild5:
2993 case OPC_MoveChild6: case OPC_MoveChild7: {
2994 unsigned ChildNo = Opcode-OPC_MoveChild0;

3574 // If the code reached this point, then the match failed. See if there is
3575 // another child to try in the current 'Scope', otherwise pop it until we
3576 // find a case to check.

3586 // Restore the interpreter state back to the point where the scope was
3587 // formed.
3588 MatchScope &LastScope = MatchScopes.back();
3589 RecordedNodes.resize(LastScope.NumRecordedNodes);
3590 NodeStack.clear();
3591 NodeStack.append(LastScope.NodeStack.begin(), LastScope.NodeStack.end());
3592 N = NodeStack.back();
3593
3594 if (LastScope.NumMatchedMemRefs != MatchedMemRefs.size())
3595 MatchedMemRefs.resize(LastScope.NumMatchedMemRefs);
3596 MatcherIndex = LastScope.FailIndex;
3597
3598 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Continuing at " << MatcherIndex << "\n");
3599
3600 InputChain = LastScope.InputChain;
3601 InputGlue = LastScope.InputGlue;
3602 if (!LastScope.HasChainNodesMatched)
3603 ChainNodesMatched.clear();
3604
3605 // Check to see what the offset is at the new MatcherIndex. If it is zero
3606 // we have reached the end of this scope, otherwise we have another child
3607 // in the current scope to try.
3608 unsigned NumToSkip = MatcherTable[MatcherIndex++];
3609 if (NumToSkip & 128)
3610 NumToSkip = GetVBR(NumToSkip, MatcherTable, MatcherIndex);
3611
3612 // If we have another child in this scope to match, update FailIndex and
3613 // try it.
3614 if (NumToSkip != 0) {
3615 LastScope.FailIndex = MatcherIndex+NumToSkip;
3616 break;
3617 }
3618
3619 // End of this scope, pop it and try the next child in the containing
3620 // scope.
3621 MatchScopes.pop_back();
3622 }
3623 }
3624}
3625
3626bool SelectionDAGISel::isOrEquivalentToAdd(const SDNode *N) const {
3627 assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::OR && "Unexpected opcode");
3628 auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
3629 if (!C)
3630 return false;
3631
3632 // Detect when "or" is used to add an offset to a stack object.
3633 if (auto *FN = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))) {
3634 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo();
3635 unsigned A = MFI.getObjectAlignment(FN->getIndex());
3636 assert(isPowerOf2_32(A) && "Unexpected alignment");
3637 int32_t Off = C->getSExtValue();
3638 // If the alleged offset fits in the zero bits guaranteed by
3639 // the alignment, then this or is really an add.
3640 return (Off >= 0) && (((A - 1) & Off) == unsigned(Off));
3641 }
3642 return false;
3643}

3645void SelectionDAGISel::CannotYetSelect(SDNode *N) {
3646 std::string msg;
3647 raw_string_ostream Msg(msg);
3648 Msg << "Cannot select: ";
3649
3650 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN &&
3651 N->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN &&
3652 N->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID) {
3653 N->printrFull(Msg, CurDAG);
3654 Msg << "\nIn function: " << MF->getName();
3655 } else {
3656 bool HasInputChain = N->getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::Other;
3657 unsigned iid =
3658 cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(HasInputChain))->getZExtValue();
3659 if (iid < Intrinsic::num_intrinsics)
3660 Msg << "intrinsic %" << Intrinsic::getName((Intrinsic::ID)iid, None);
3661 else if (const TargetIntrinsicInfo *TII = TM.getIntrinsicInfo())
3662 Msg << "target intrinsic %" << TII->getName(iid);
3663 else
3664 Msg << "unknown intrinsic #" << iid;
3665 }
3666 report_fatal_error(Msg.str());
3667}
